        "Vertebrate = an animal with a backbone; invertebrate = an animal without one.",
        "An adult human has 24 movable vertebrae (7 neck, 12 mid-back, 5 lower back) plus the fused sacrum and tailbone; a child can usually feel about 17 clearly through the skin.",
        "Fish, frogs, snakes, birds, and mammals are all vertebrates — five very different bodies built on the same basic plan.",
        "A snail, an insect, and a sponge have no internal skeleton at all — they are invertebrates.",
        "The backbone is also called the spine or spinal column; each single bone in it is a vertebra.",
