        "Reptile = backboned animal with dry, scaly skin, laying leathery or hard-shelled eggs on land.",
        "Both amphibians and reptiles are cold-blooded — their body temperature follows the temperature around them, so reptiles bask in the sun to warm up and become active.",
        "Frog egg masses are jelly-like clumps with black dots; toad eggs are laid in long strings.",
        "A tadpole is a baby frog or toad living entirely in water and breathing through gills, before it grows legs and lungs.",
