      formIIA: "“A frog's egg is soft and has to stay in water or it dries out, but a reptile's egg has a shell that holds water inside it, so it can be laid anywhere on land. That's why Buckley calls the shell one of the great inventions — it let backboned animals finally live away from ponds and rivers for good.”",
      journal: "Copywork of Job 12:7–8 — first verse today, second in the morning (IA); both verses in one sitting, best hand, cursive if introduced (IIA).",
