      formIIA: "“A frog's eggs have no shell, only a jelly coating, so they'd dry out and die on land — they must stay in water. A chicken egg has a hard shell that holds moisture inside, so it can be laid anywhere on land. That's why frogs are still tied to ponds even as adults, while chickens and reptiles aren't.”",
      journal: "The colored life-cycle wheel with one sentence (IA), or the wheel plus a full paragraph on why frog eggs must stay in water (IIA).",
